<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>TSI 92-08-04 - Welding on Navistar Vehicles</stitle>
    <tsi id="tsi920804" tsitype="truck">
        <tsinumber>92-08-04</tsinumber>
        <tsidate>May, 1992</tsidate>
        <subjectfile>ELECTRICAL</subjectfile>
        <subjectgroup>
            <subject>Welding on Navistar Vehicles</subject>
        </subjectgroup>
        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>Navistar vehicles are currently equipped with various electronic components including, but not
                    limited to:
                </para>
                <randlist type="bullet">
                    <item>
                        <para>Instrumentation</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>ABS Modules</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Brake Warning Module</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Engine Control Modules</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Transmission Control Modules</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Glow Plug Module</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Panel Light Dimmer</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Windshield Wiper Control (Intermittent)</para>
                    </item>
                    <item>
                        <para>Radio</para>
                    </item>
                </randlist>
                <para>Excessive voltage or current applied to electronic components may damage or destroy them,
                    resulting in expensive repairs.
                </para>
                <specpara>
                    <caution>
                        <para>To avoid damage to vehicle electronic components, disconnect both battery positive (+) and
                            negative (-) cables prior to welding. Attach the welding ground cable as close as possible
                            to the part being welded. If necessary to weld close to an electronic component, it is
                            recommended that the electronic component be temporarily removed.
                        </para>
                    </caution>
                </specpara>
                <para>Electronic component failures caused by excessive voltage or current will be denied warranty
                    reimbursement.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
    </tsi>
</isis>
